The paper is about visible and infrared image fusion, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and image processing (cs.MM). The use of infrared images also suggests a connection to the subfield of infrared imaging (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the performance of different fusion algorithms, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI).
